WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:00.156 --> 00:00:02.832
Ever since you began
to build your empire.

2
00:00:02.856 --> 00:00:04.898
you've had a crutch to lean on.

3
00:00:04.923 --> 00:00:07.475
I swear in the name of Almighty God.

4
00:00:07.500 --> 00:00:09.796
I will take revenge on Tommy Shelby.

5
00:00:09.820 --> 00:00:12.873
That. my friend.
is the finest opium in the world.

6
00:00:12.897 --> 00:00:14.614
Perhaps we can meet after you've spoken

7
00:00:14.638 --> 00:00:16.410
with your wife's uncle. Jack Nelson.

8
00:00:16.434 --> 00:00:18.956
Tommy Shelby wants
to do business with Jack Nelson?

9
00:00:18.980 --> 00:00:20.996
So. speak to your uncle
and get me out of here.

10
00:00:21.020 --> 00:00:22.636
If he doesn't want to buy my opium.

11
00:00:22.660 --> 00:00:24.676
I will sell to the East Boston Jews.

12
00:00:24.700 --> 00:00:26.516
It's Ruby. She's not well.

13
00:00:26.540 --> 00:00:27.636
I'm coming home.

14
00:00:33.540 --> 00:00:38.423
There will be a war in this
family and one of you will die.

15
00:00:39.500 --> 00:00:42.796
You've been too busy to
punish the people that killed her.

16
00:00:43.552 --> 00:00:45.272
How is the family?

17
00:00:55.860 --> 00:00:57.020
Daddy.

18
00:01:01.460 --> 00:01:02.780
Hello. Ruby.

19
00:01:03.980 --> 00:01:05.316
Come here.

20
00:01:05.340 --> 00:01:06.743
Let me see you.

21
00:01:07.580 --> 00:01:10.540
I missed you. I missed you.

22
00:01:11.620 --> 00:01:13.276
That is a Black Madonna.

23
00:01:13.300 --> 00:01:15.076
What presents did you get us. Dad?

24
00:01:15.100 --> 00:01:16.516
Son.

25
00:01:16.540 --> 00:01:18.076
She's all better. Tommy.

26
00:01:18.100 --> 00:01:20.243
You came back for nothing.

27
00:01:23.740 --> 00:01:25.220
But I'm glad you're back.

28
00:01:27.260 --> 00:01:29.509
Right. before we do anything else.

29
00:01:29.533 --> 00:01:31.716
we're going to go for a drive. OK?

30
00:01:31.740 --> 00:01:33.236
- Let's go.
- What about me?

31
00:01:33.260 --> 00:01:34.756
Yeah. you can come too. come on.

32
00:01:34.780 --> 00:01:36.636
A drive where?

33
00:01:37.393 --> 00:01:39.544
I've asked the driver to take
us to see Dr Robert.

34
00:01:39.568 --> 00:01:41.956
- I want him to have a look at Ruby.
- Why. love?

35
00:01:41.980 --> 00:01:45.180
The appointment is in one hour.
you can stay here or you can come.

36
00:01:46.540 --> 00:01:47.863
Right.

37
00:01:48.773 --> 00:01:50.653
Right. let's go.

38
00:02:05.023 --> 00:02:10.048
Synced & corrected by -robtor-
www.addic7ed.com

39
00:02:40.260 --> 00:02:41.623
Tommy?

40
00:02:42.326 --> 00:02:43.526
Yeah?

41
00:02:45.665 --> 00:02:48.443
It was all good. Everything was clear.

42
00:02:49.260 --> 00:02:50.460
That is a relief.

43
00:02:51.660 --> 00:02:54.276
- That's a relief.
- Yeah.

44
00:02:55.028 --> 00:02:56.148
Driver's bringing the car round.

45
00:02:56.173 --> 00:02:57.590
Daddy.

46
00:02:59.033 --> 00:03:00.273
Hiya.

47
00:03:03.300 --> 00:03:04.340
Come here.

48
00:03:11.077 --> 00:03:12.597
When did you last sleep?

49
00:03:14.830 --> 00:03:17.383
Not much since we last spoke
on the phone.

50
00:03:18.443 --> 00:03:21.213
Well. now you know Ruby's all clear.
you can sleep.

51
00:03:21.237 --> 00:03:22.483
Yeah.

52
00:03:24.837 --> 00:03:28.253
Lizzie. I am very happy that
Ruby's results are clear.

53
00:03:28.530 --> 00:03:29.970
But still you won't sleep.

54
00:03:31.477 --> 00:03:34.813
I will speak to Johnny
and I will speak to Esmeralda.

55
00:03:40.637 --> 00:03:41.917
We could be on holiday.

56
00:03:43.076 --> 00:03:44.916
We could be up a mountain in America.

57
00:03:46.109 --> 00:03:47.869
That wouldn't have been possible.

58
00:03:48.723 --> 00:03:52.563
The man I'm dealing with is coming
to London. I need to be there.

59
00:03:53.849 --> 00:03:54.969
No escape.

60
00:03:56.630 --> 00:04:00.366
We will escape. Lizzie.
One last deal to be done.

61
00:04:00.477 --> 00:04:03.533
It'll be difficult.
Difficulties are to be expected.

62
00:04:03.557 --> 00:04:06.683
This is why I must move
from item to item.

63
00:04:11.716 --> 00:04:12.916
Do you feel that?

64
00:04:14.043 --> 00:04:15.443
Do you feel anything?

65
00:04:16.717 --> 00:04:20.317
You know. you talk as if you're
watching everything on a screen.

66
00:04:24.157 --> 00:04:26.453
When we go home. When we go home.

67
00:04:26.477 --> 00:04:29.677
we'll give the kids to Frances.
and then you and me will go to bed.

68
00:04:31.637 --> 00:04:33.493
And I will be the next item.

69
00:04:33.517 --> 00:04:36.493
- That's how it feels now. Tommy.
- Yeah.

70
00:04:36.517 --> 00:04:37.757
Everything on a list.

71
00:04:44.477 --> 00:04:46.877
- Hey. baby.
- When are we going home?

72
00:05:06.723 --> 00:05:08.923
Tommy? Tommy?

73
00:05:21.637 --> 00:05:23.917
Tommy? What's happened?

74
00:05:25.037 --> 00:05:26.477
Fuck. fuck.

75
00:05:27.597 --> 00:05:28.797
Fuck.

76
00:05:30.477 --> 00:05:32.413
Tommy. Come here. Come here.

77
00:05:32.437 --> 00:05:33.637
What's happened?

78
00:05:36.157 --> 00:05:37.437
Tommy.

79
00:05:59.837 --> 00:06:01.503
It is four years...

80
00:06:02.730 --> 00:06:04.466
...one month and six days

81
00:06:04.896 --> 00:06:06.096
since I had a drink.

82
00:06:07.837 --> 00:06:09.677
My head is clear.

83
00:06:11.157 --> 00:06:12.597
I am myself.

84
00:06:14.910 --> 00:06:16.110
Is this the first time?

85
00:06:18.757 --> 00:06:21.157
Once on the ship back. Not as bad.

86
00:06:23.890 --> 00:06:25.450
Tommy...

87
00:06:26.637 --> 00:06:28.503
...you need to see a doctor.

88
00:06:30.290 --> 00:06:31.890
I've work to do.

89
00:06:33.997 --> 00:06:35.517
It's the work that's to blame.

90
00:06:36.763 --> 00:06:38.803
The people you meet.
the lies that you tell.

91
00:06:41.637 --> 00:06:44.597
We're going to keep going till
the Boston business is done.

92
00:06:45.770 --> 00:06:46.810
Then we rest.

93
00:06:48.643 --> 00:06:50.903
Then we Peaky Blinders fucking rest.

94
00:06:54.916 --> 00:06:58.423
Comrades. before we
end this planning meeting

95
00:06:58.448 --> 00:07:00.824
and send you out into the rain...

96
00:07:01.243 --> 00:07:02.683
...we have a surprise.

97
00:07:03.677 --> 00:07:06.973
He just arrived back from
a trade mission to America.

98
00:07:06.997 --> 00:07:08.333
He came back early

99
00:07:08.357 --> 00:07:11.923
and he has insisted on addressing
you volunteers in person.

100
00:07:12.757 --> 00:07:14.333
Comrades.

101
00:07:14.357 --> 00:07:16.533
your Labour representative
for South Birmingham.

102
00:07:16.557 --> 00:07:18.139
Mr Thomas Shelby MP. OBE.

103
00:07:36.280 --> 00:07:38.280
_

104
00:07:43.723 --> 00:07:48.303
I bring with me on
the train from London...

105
00:07:49.037 --> 00:07:52.163
...a message from Westminster.

106
00:07:53.117 --> 00:07:56.350
No. No. no. no. not a message.

107
00:07:56.374 --> 00:07:57.637
Not a message.

108
00:07:59.317 --> 00:08:01.293
An instruction. in fact.

109
00:08:03.557 --> 00:08:05.002
You must be silent.

110
00:08:10.029 --> 00:08:11.549
You must say nothing.

111
00:08:13.370 --> 00:08:17.283
Say nothing about the present
situation in this city.

112
00:08:18.636 --> 00:08:20.612
Say nothing about hunger.

113
00:08:20.717 --> 00:08:22.773
Say nothing about jobs.

114
00:08:22.797 --> 00:08:25.293
Say nothing about pay.

115
00:08:25.317 --> 00:08:28.173
But those in greener pastures.

116
00:08:28.623 --> 00:08:30.051
they may speak.

117
00:08:31.317 --> 00:08:32.754
They may raise their voices.

118
00:08:34.237 --> 00:08:36.773
But here in the smoke.
you men and women.

119
00:08:36.797 --> 00:08:38.573
Irish and Italian

120
00:08:38.597 --> 00:08:41.983
and English who support
the Socialist cause...

121
00:08:42.797 --> 00:08:45.093
And even your socialist cats and
dogs and canaries.

122
00:08:47.277 --> 00:08:49.413
...you must hush.

123
00:08:49.437 --> 00:08:54.213
Because the King. and all the King's
horses and all the King's men...

124
00:08:55.368 --> 00:08:57.203
...want you to be silent.

125
00:08:57.957 --> 00:09:00.893
But it is you. my friends.
who must suffer

126
00:09:00.917 --> 00:09:04.733
the cuts in wages and
in welfare and in dignity.

127
00:09:04.757 --> 00:09:06.493
And you must not complain.

128
00:09:06.517 --> 00:09:08.283
because that would be unpatriotic.

129
00:09:09.117 --> 00:09:12.213
You soldiers. who have fought in France.

130
00:09:12.237 --> 00:09:14.413
you are traitors if you speak up.

131
00:09:14.437 --> 00:09:18.893
You veterans of their wars
and their booms and their busts.

132
00:09:18.917 --> 00:09:21.213
it is you who must take the blows.

133
00:09:21.237 --> 00:09:23.835
and carry the burdens
for the sake of those

134
00:09:23.859 --> 00:09:26.853
in greener pastures who bellow at you...

135
00:09:28.758 --> 00:09:30.213
..."Silence".

136
00:09:32.157 --> 00:09:33.973
Well. watch this. comrades.

137
00:09:33.997 --> 00:09:35.637
I will not be silent.

138
00:09:36.634 --> 00:09:38.253
Not this Englishman.

139
00:09:45.997 --> 00:09:47.813
No silence from me.

140
00:09:47.837 --> 00:09:49.733
No silence from me.

141
00:09:49.757 --> 00:09:53.413
because I have heard your voices
when you come to me

142
00:09:53.437 --> 00:09:56.853
and tell me about
the cries of your hungry children.

143
00:09:57.457 --> 00:10:00.813
and I will gather up every
single one of those cries

144
00:10:00.837 --> 00:10:04.813
and I will take 'em with me
on the train to Westminster...

145
00:10:06.220 --> 00:10:09.133
...and I will let them out
of the bag in the House of Commons.

146
00:10:09.157 --> 00:10:11.213
and let them try to silence that. eh?

147
00:10:28.277 --> 00:10:31.197
Shouldn't that involve
some sharing of the burden?

148
00:10:32.496 --> 00:10:35.303
All of us taking
a smaller slice of the cake. eh?

149
00:10:36.197 --> 00:10:38.933
After all. it's bloody us
who bakes the cake

150
00:10:38.957 --> 00:10:42.003
and makes the cars and melts the metal.

151
00:10:42.597 --> 00:10:45.493
And the King. remember him.

152
00:10:45.923 --> 00:10:48.213
the man who ordered all of this.

153
00:10:48.237 --> 00:10:50.523
shouldn't he be taking some of the cuts?

154
00:10:51.317 --> 00:10:53.213
Eh. some of the blows?

155
00:10:53.237 --> 00:10:56.093
Some of the pain? No or yes?

156
00:10:56.117 --> 00:10:57.837
YES!

157
00:11:08.677 --> 00:11:10.173
Hush.

158
00:11:10.197 --> 00:11:12.653
Hush. you working men and women.

159
00:11:12.776 --> 00:11:14.096
Silence.

160
00:11:16.756 --> 00:11:17.983
Good.

161
00:11:18.637 --> 00:11:20.103
Save your voices.

162
00:11:21.536 --> 00:11:25.552
You are going to need them on
Saturday when we rally together

163
00:11:25.577 --> 00:11:27.433
at the Bull Ring Market...

164
00:11:28.535 --> 00:11:30.743
...and together. we'll raise the roof.

165
00:11:31.317 --> 00:11:33.437
we'll break the damned silence...

166
00:11:35.527 --> 00:11:37.933
...and bring down this broken
government.

167
00:11:44.329 --> 00:11:46.425
Tommy. Tommy.

168
00:11:46.450 --> 00:11:48.450
Tommy. Tommy...

169
00:11:54.429 --> 00:11:55.469
Thank you.

170
00:11:58.570 --> 00:11:59.810
Laura McKee.

171
00:12:00.957 --> 00:12:04.133
Battalion Commander. Fermanagh IRA.

172
00:12:04.463 --> 00:12:06.413
You missed the first and second act.

173
00:12:06.437 --> 00:12:07.671
Thank you for coming. Mr Shelby.

174
00:12:07.695 --> 00:12:09.035
Thank you. Thank you.

175
00:12:09.059 --> 00:12:10.597
The third act was enough.

176
00:12:13.317 --> 00:12:15.613
You both have reasons to hate me

177
00:12:15.883 --> 00:12:17.813
and to want to seek revenge
for the killing of...

178
00:12:17.837 --> 00:12:19.037
Sh.

179
00:12:20.756 --> 00:12:22.223
Gypsy tradition.

180
00:12:23.797 --> 00:12:28.523
We do not mention the name of
the dead in company.

181
00:12:33.197 --> 00:12:34.933
Laura McKee.

182
00:12:34.957 --> 00:12:36.733
in the Shelby family.

183
00:12:36.757 --> 00:12:39.863
business comes before issues
of vengeance.

184
00:12:40.237 --> 00:12:43.317
Our beloved departed would
understand and approve.

185
00:12:45.117 --> 00:12:46.643
Let's go. boys.

186
00:12:46.668 --> 00:12:48.964
Our agreement was we meet
in a crowded place.

187
00:12:49.223 --> 00:12:50.423
No need for crowds.

188
00:12:51.570 --> 00:12:52.610
We need you alive.

189
00:12:55.263 --> 00:12:56.743
After you.

190
00:13:20.517 --> 00:13:24.163
You know. Mr Shelby. even though
we've been doing business for a while.

191
00:13:24.797 --> 00:13:26.597
we've never met in person.

192
00:13:27.677 --> 00:13:31.443
You spoke with passion and compassion.

193
00:13:33.750 --> 00:13:36.166
You understand forgiveness

194
00:13:36.529 --> 00:13:38.129
and you drink water.

195
00:13:39.877 --> 00:13:42.773
Yet I heard from many reliable sources

196
00:13:42.797 --> 00:13:46.717
that you have a reputation
for moral turpitude.

197
00:13:49.957 --> 00:13:51.483
"Moral turpitude".

198
00:13:53.237 --> 00:13:54.877
It's a good name for a racehorse.

199
00:13:56.143 --> 00:13:57.373
You don't know what it means?

200
00:13:57.397 --> 00:13:58.803
I know what it means.

201
00:13:59.517 --> 00:14:01.077
It means you fuck people.

202
00:14:02.509 --> 00:14:05.005
Fuck people over. Don't give a fuck.

203
00:14:05.117 --> 00:14:06.693
It means you covet and steal

204
00:14:06.717 --> 00:14:10.023
and burn all principles
for the sake of self-interest.

205
00:14:11.997 --> 00:14:14.933
Well. I'm changing. Laura McKee.

206
00:14:14.957 --> 00:14:17.243
and my organisation is also changing.

207
00:14:21.997 --> 00:14:23.883
So. what happened in Boston?

208
00:14:25.077 --> 00:14:26.783
Jack Nelson said no.

209
00:14:27.157 --> 00:14:30.117
Are we accepting "no" as an answer?

210
00:14:31.917 --> 00:14:35.213
These are letters written to

211
00:14:35.237 --> 00:14:38.063
and by Jack Nelson
over the last three months.

212
00:14:51.236 --> 00:14:52.356
This...

213
00:14:53.557 --> 00:14:56.837
This is a private letter from
the President of the United States.

214
00:14:58.157 --> 00:14:59.757
Where the fuck did you get this?

215
00:15:00.797 --> 00:15:03.253
My racehorse. Moral Turpitude.

216
00:15:03.277 --> 00:15:05.343
is just one of many in my stables.

217
00:15:06.077 --> 00:15:09.053
Sometimes even now I'll
take her out for a run.

218
00:15:09.243 --> 00:15:11.923
if there is a good cause that
requires her services.

219
00:15:16.637 --> 00:15:19.213
Jack Nelson's coming to London.

220
00:15:19.237 --> 00:15:23.453
Officially. he's coming
to buy liquor import licenses.

221
00:15:23.856 --> 00:15:26.595
Unofficially. he's on
a fact-finding mission.

222
00:15:27.563 --> 00:15:31.133
He's come to measure the strength of
support for fascism in Britain.

223
00:15:31.157 --> 00:15:32.997
He'll report back to the President.

224
00:15:35.837 --> 00:15:37.357
And how does that help us?

225
00:15:40.569 --> 00:15:42.665
In this letter to his son.

226
00:15:42.877 --> 00:15:46.143
Jack Nelson expresses
strong support for fascism.

227
00:15:46.597 --> 00:15:50.293
In this letter to a friend in Berlin.

228
00:15:50.317 --> 00:15:54.503
he says some. erm.
interesting things about Jews.

229
00:15:56.797 --> 00:15:59.333
He's not coming to Europe to find facts.

230
00:15:59.357 --> 00:16:02.323
He's coming to find proof
that fascism will prevail.

231
00:16:03.676 --> 00:16:07.923
And you and I are going
to help him in that task.

232
00:16:12.009 --> 00:16:13.609
I thought you were a socialist.

233
00:16:17.197 --> 00:16:18.463
Well...

234
00:16:19.077 --> 00:16:20.333
...since I've entered politics.

235
00:16:20.357 --> 00:16:22.853
I've learned that
the line doesn't go out from

236
00:16:22.877 --> 00:16:24.933
the middle to the left and the right.

237
00:16:24.957 --> 00:16:26.557
It goes in a circle.

238
00:16:27.757 --> 00:16:28.797
I'll show you.

239
00:16:32.277 --> 00:16:34.573
You go far enough left.

240
00:16:34.597 --> 00:16:37.933
eventually you'll meet someone
who has gone far enough right

241
00:16:37.957 --> 00:16:39.597
to get to the same place.

242
00:16:42.397 --> 00:16:44.173
Working-class socialists like me.

243
00:16:44.197 --> 00:16:46.333
working-class nationalists like you.

244
00:16:46.357 --> 00:16:47.733
The result?

245
00:16:48.129 --> 00:16:49.729
National Socialism.

246
00:16:51.630 --> 00:16:53.003
And that's me.

247
00:16:54.416 --> 00:16:55.983
in the middle.

248
00:16:57.336 --> 00:17:01.703
Just a man trying to make an honest
living in a very dark world.

249
00:17:05.917 --> 00:17:08.423
You have friends in Dublin. Laura McKee.

250
00:17:08.797 --> 00:17:11.563
who are actively fighting for
a Fascist Ireland.

251
00:17:12.236 --> 00:17:15.436
And you are acting on their behalf.
ain't you?

252
00:17:17.117 --> 00:17:20.173
When Jack Nelson comes to London.

253
00:17:20.197 --> 00:17:23.853
I can give him access to Oswald Mosley

254
00:17:23.877 --> 00:17:27.373
and to Fascist sympathisers
in the House of Commons

255
00:17:27.397 --> 00:17:29.957
and the House of Lords.
on both sides of the divide.

256
00:17:31.370 --> 00:17:32.890
Fascism is quite the thing...

257
00:17:34.950 --> 00:17:36.470
...among the very best people.

258
00:17:38.237 --> 00:17:42.023
And with your help.
I can also offer him Dublin.

259
00:17:45.829 --> 00:17:50.245
And you think this will allow us
to ship our merchandise to Boston?

260
00:17:50.357 --> 00:17:51.683
Perhaps.

261
00:17:52.310 --> 00:17:55.243
There may be other
benefits for your cause.

262
00:17:56.757 --> 00:18:00.573
All you have to do
is sit with Jack Nelson

263
00:18:00.597 --> 00:18:03.523
and talk to him about a new "golden age"

264
00:18:03.877 --> 00:18:06.183
and let him put a pin in
the map of Ireland

265
